President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Henry C. Eickelberg will be appointed as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation. Sachin Dev Pavithran will be appointed as a member of the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Board. Shelley Siegel will also be appointed as a member of the Architectural and Transportation Barriers Compliance Board. Wayne A. I. Frederick will be appointed as a member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities. Lastly, Janice Bryant Howroyd will be appointed as a member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and looks forward to working with them.